<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-710-598  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 710 598.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  August 6 1990 n312 p12(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bells fight FCC ruling. (Bell regional holding companies opposeFCC ruling that would enable long distance carriers to recoverdamages from them)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Bell regional holding companies (RBOCs) are urging a federalappeals court to reverse a FCC ruling that empowers long distancecarriers and other companies to recover damages from the telephonecompanies.andP;  The damages, amounting to millions of dollars, areowed because the RBOCs earned more on interstate access servicesthan their authorized rate of return allowed.andP;  AT and T and MCICommunications Corp led the legal offensive against the RBOC ,which is concerned with the period between Oct 1, 1985, and Dec31, 1986.andP;  The precise amount owed by the RBOCs has not beendetermined yet by the FCC.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (cases)MCI Communications Corp. (cases).andO;Ticker:    MCIC; T.andO;Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionLegal IssuesLong-Distance Telephone ServicesGovernment Regulation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>